title: Duluth's Forbort Expected to Make NHL Debut
text:
Duluth's Forbort Expected to Make NHL Debut 
By Zach Schneider Duluth's Forbort Expected to Make NHL Debut October 15, 2015 Updated Oct 15, 2015 at 5:16 PM CDT 
Los Angeles, CA (NNCNOW.com) --- Duluth, Minn. native Derek Forbort is expected to make his NHL debut on Friday night with the Los Angeles Kings against his home-state team in the Minnesota Wild, head coach Darryl Sutter told media on Thursday. 
Forbort has been on the Kings' 23-man roster since the start of the regular season, but he hasn't played in any of the team's first three contests. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
His debut could come Friday because of an injury to Matt Greene, although Sutter wasn't 100 percent sure that Forbort would be in the lineup. 
The former Duluth East standout was a first-round pick in the 2010 NHL Entry Draft, and he has spent the past two seasons playing with the AHL's Manchester Monarchs. 
Last winter, Forbort tallied four goals and 11 assists with Manchester.
